caption: Great place best Italian food I've ever had in my life

The wonderful aroma of garlic roasting in butter as you open the door to this upstairs gem on Frenchman street. Don't be fooled by the well worn stairs, their kitchen delivers amazingly delicious options. The rack of lamb was cooked perfectly, surrounded by a delicious sauce of butter, garlic & spices. The lamb flavor was there and it definitely wasn't too gamey. Their veal dishes are amazingly tender and the preparations range from simple picatta, to spinach & lemon sauce or their intoxicating Ocean Sauce (shrimp & crawfish in a light, creamy sauce). We were all pleasantly fill but couldn't leave before sharing a slice of delightfully refreshing lemon cello cake.
Small, intimate space. EXCELLENT service. I had the rack of lamb...best I've ever had.
Amazing, as always. Luckily, Chef was in a good mood, so we go pink sauce on our pasta and Ocean Sauce on the lamb. Couldn't have asked for a better dinner or night!

I was born and raised in NOLA.   I cant imagine finding better/fresher seafood and the Italian meets Creole fusion is outstanding.   Because I have not lived near the gulf coast since graduating from LSU, I CRAVE fresh seafood (I have tasted all the other non-seafood dishes and they are great).    I go to Adolfo's every time I return home and am never disappointed.   If you don't like their fresh fish with Ocean Sauce, you are from too far away.  :)   I found this place bc my fishing guide about 10 years ago put me onto it before Adolfo's became a staple.    He knew the chef (at that time it was Gotto) and actually sold fresh fish to him that would be served the night it was caught.   Many great restaurants in my home town.  This is one of them for sure.
My favorite all time dining of anywhere I've been in this country!
Absolutely delicious food and great ambiance. A hidden gem and we absolutely will be back the next time we visit.
Always the best.  And don't miss the ocean sauce for your food.
We come here every time we visit N.O., always delicious! Not a fancy place but very relaxed. I tried the crab cannelloni this time, yum.
We had a great time at Adolfo's! The staff is adorable and the food delicious :) The mussels were amazing in particular. Have a go at the cocktails too!

This little venue is doing it right. Intimate vibe; food cooked to order in a small kitchen (you can see a lot of the action). Service was great. Call ahead for a reservation; they bent over backwards to get us in.  Honestly, the food was not the best I've had recently but I would go back and try some other items. They obviously care about their craft and that goes far in my book. The rack of lamb was clearly a signature and impressed. The salad had a great house dressing but was very small. Frog legs app was just OK (sauce appeared oily or broken).

Ate here tonight! Was very very good. Get a reservation and sit upstairs to get the full experience!!!!  I can’t wait to come here again. I’m bringing my momma next time !  For the people that left bad reviews. Y’all are dumb. This place is a Gem
Food was delicious!

I would not recommend this restaurant. My husband and I came here while we were on vacation in New Orleans. I got the cannelloni and he got the Italian sausage marinara. Nether meal was very good. Even the bread was bland and low-quality.
Great food and cozy atmosphere! Servers are so nice
The mussels are a don't miss. Have every time we are in town
The food is amazing and I highly recommend you go...SOON! I visited for my 4th wedding anniversary with two other couples! We tried so many different dishes and shared with a smile!
For a little hidden place, the food was different but very good and fair priced
One of my favorite spots for quality italian food. this place will surprise you. this place has an awesome atmosphere.

Always give a 5 star so glad they are doing takeout wish they would keep it but I always get the veal stacie...this time there was coating on my veal it had NEVER had it on there before..I guess they figured it was a togo and I wouldn't notice but since I eat here regularly for every personal occasion I noticed...was really bummed if i were inside i would have sent it back....

I love this place!!! The atmosphere is great, from the front of the house to the back of the house from hostess to waiting staff to the kitchen the service is impeccable, & the food is absolutely delicious & to die for... Thank you so very much for an amazing experience Adolfo's...
Their food is incredible! The salmon and lamb are amazing! And I'm vegan! It is very small. So get in line early. It gets a little noisy when the room fills up. But it still feels romantic.
Always fun and tasty

The best of the best in the French Quarter. What ever you decide to eat, make certain you get Ocean Sauce. The atmosphere, service, ambiance, vibe, aroma, food, and one on one attention is worth it's weight in gold. Make reservations and parking is close and not expensive.

If I could give them 10 stars, I would, and this is due to how unbelievably amazing their stuffed flounder is. Yes, it was a little bit of a wait to be seated, but that is nothing compared to the wait I'll have before I get to go there again being that I'm from Texas.  Please go there and try that stuffed flounder....for me. And if you're the chef and you are reading this review, if you happen to have a pointer or two on how I could closely duplicate cooking this at home, that would be much appreciated.

Our waiter was James. Looked at the menu, things on the menu were like 16-27 dollars. Told us about the “specials” lamb and flounder, did not mention price and we didn’t ask. We ordered the specials, which is a big up sell to say the least which we didn’t find out til we got the bill.  The food was very good, except the pasta start was noodles with a watery tomato sauce, quite flavorless. Cash only place, took out extra money before the meal. Got the bill it was just under $200 before tax. The lamb was 39 a plate! Gave the waiter a $25 tip. He returned it to us and made it known to us he expected a $50 tip! Wow the arrogance. His service was ok, but here’s the thing, it doesn’t take any more expertise to set down a plate that cost $40 as it does to set down a plate that costs $17.  And who deserves an extra $50 for less than an hours service?! The blues and Jazz bands that play in the bars work a whole lot harder for their tips and get way less per hour. They are skilled musicians. Healthcare workers sure don’t get tipped an extra $50 per hour by all their patients for the care they receive. The absolute arrogance of this waiter and reading other reviews this is common place at this establishment. I will never go back. With all the amazing food choices in New Orleans that give great service with no attitude, it’s a no brainer.
They lived up to their reputation. We heard about them half way across the country from multiple people. The New York strip with ocean sauce was to die for! We also loved the steak bruschetta.

caption: Undeniably the finest restaurant in NOLA!
The rack of lamb was amazing!
The best lamb I have ever had.
The food was delicious and definitely worth the long wait. Go early.  Seating is limited. We enjoyed the bar downstairs while we waited!
Best meal in New Orleans. The rack of lamb and stuffed fish was absolutely incredible. The bar downstairs with live music made the 2 hour wait easy.
Most amazing meal I've had in NOLA. Would highly recommend this place for anyone wanting amazing seafood.
Truly unique combination of Creole and Italian.  Try anything with ocean sauce.
I absolutely L O V E this place. I had the mussels and they are absolutely the best mussels I’ve ever had ever. I would come back to New Orleans specifically for these mussels
Awful. The pasta was watered down marinara sauce. Never been more disappointed

Word of mouth can be a powerful marketing play.  When NOLA locals said some of the best New Orleans food can be found in this quaint house just outside the quarter; I was all in.  Well at least half that story is accurate, it is in a quaint house outside the quarter.  Here is case where the hype does not live up.  Let me tell you why.  My meal order included the mussels, wine and the lamb.  Pasta comes with the meal.  The mussels were a highlight and wonderfully  plump and flavorful.  The pasta was nothing more than some overcooked noodles with a splash of tomato sauce and some cheese.  Very basic and void of discernible flavor.   The lamb arrived in a pool of juice with rosemary swimming around.  The lamb was meaty and the rosemary added to meat, but it was not anything I would rave about.  The meal was not the least bit refined nor fine dining.  The server receives an award for up selling which he did with great enthusiasm.   All his recommendations were some of the most expensive items available and my meal alone cost $70 with only one glass of wine.  A coincidence?  I am not sure, but our table fell for it and ironically, this quaint Italian restaurant became my most expensive meal in New Orleans, but certainly not one of the better meals.  I feel a tinge of the overused word tourist trap, but I guess you can decide.
Amazing food. Worth the hour long wait to get seated. I had the stuffed tilapia with seafood sauce - one of the specials for the night.
The restaurant itself was small and upstairs  but I liked the atmosphere and the food was delicious.  Our waitress was friendly and attentive.
This place is my favorite in NOLA. Lamb is os good and inspirational (I replicated at home, but not as good). Stuffed flounder is amazing.  Down to earth, simple place. You cannot go wrong here.
More Creole than Italian in some aspects but not a bad thing! Small, intimate place with great flavors. Go with the ocean sauce on any protein and it's a whirlwind of flavors and spices.
Great food and service but be ready to wait if you are coming on a weekend evening.

Mussels, rack of lamb, stuffed fish with ocean sauce! Hot Dang! Best meal of the trip. Best lamb of my life! Wonderful and friendly service in a cozy space. Great music and drinks at the bar downstairs for before and after dinner. Must try!
A little hard to find on the 2nd floor but well worth it. One of the best meals I've had in some time…
Ocean sauce!!!
Adolfos was fun and the food was delicious! Our server was fun and helpful!
Food high quality. Worth the wait for a table! Service is outstanding and food is the best we had in a week visiting NOLA. 1000% recommend!

Told waitress I had food allergies and can’t have Cheeses. Watched cook sprinkle cheese on my meal. Waitress noticed this before she brought it to me. So she mixed up the cheese into the sauce and brought it to me. Told her I saw what she did and she said “ no big deal it was barely any cheese”. Made them make me a new one still. Listened to waitress complain about me to the other staff members.  Not worth the wait for the price you pay.
The service was good but the food was not. The bread was like Texas toast. The eggplant Parmesan was not that at all. It was sliced eggplant it seemed like steamed, with way too much subpar cheese.

We had a lamb and past, the lamb was marinated well and comes tender. The beat lamb i have ever had. I highly recommend this place. One thing need to keep in mind, no reservation fist come first served, plane few hours ahead of your date
Very small upstairs and somewhat hidden location. The food and service were both very good. Cash only but there is an ATM in the dining room.

This place is amazing. A delightful cozy atmosphere and the food was scrumptious! Our party had the escargot, mussels, cannelloni stuffed crab meat, lamb, and veal parmigiana. That veal tasted like my grandmothers. I’ve never had such good Italian food this far south. Also, wonderful hospitality and service.
Nice food
Some of the best food in the city
Please don't go when I'm hoping to get a table. It's hard for me to wait for this deliciousness.

It was busy, we had to wait 1 1/2 hour downstairs in the bar. That was fun, super fun bartender and band. Note that with Adolfo's you can only pay with CASH  (Original) We aten de meest lekkere chickenbreast met pasta van de wereld. Apart genoeg kreeg ik de pasta eerst en 20 minuten daarna de kip. Het was druk, we moesten beneden in de bar 1 1/2 uur wachten. Dat was fun, superleuke barvrouw en bandje. Let op bij Adolfo's kan je alleen met CASH betalen
Excellent food!! Ordered the stuff flounder and shrimp with ocean sauce. Was not disappointed. Very unique atmosphere. Get there early to avoid the wait.

Visiting New Orleans on a business trip and trying to find a place that everyone will like (that serves both delicious vegan and non vegan options) seemed like it would be tough. Decided to go to Adolfo's because they have pasta. Pleasantly surprised to find they do have a delicious vegan dish as well as delicious non vegan options. Tim was our server and he did a fantastic job! Really enjoyed his presentation of the restaurant and his style of serving.

Last night My new wife and I made our way down to Frenchmen Street to listen to some live music and have dinner. We came across a nondescript place with a small unlit sign called Adolfo's Restaurant. It’s above a bar and has only 10 tables. As soon as we walked in the door we knew it was the place for us. Small, intimate, and lots of character. Our waiter, James, was at the top of his game, and knew the menu inside and out. We opted to start with Mussels, and then moved on to one of the specials, which was a New York Strip, medium rare of course, topped with their Ocean Sauce. The Ocean Sauce has a light cream base with half of each, crabmeat, crawfish, shrimp, and capers. It was outstanding, as was the wine pairing and Limoncello cake for dessert. If you are headed to New Orleans, check out Adolfo’s, and definitely ask for James! It’s an evening we won’t soon forget! Highly recommend!
Super good.
Incredible from start to finish. Spectacular food (Ocean sauce is divine), knowledgeable and friendly service. Affordable fancy food in a laid back, cozy upstairs nook. Not wheelchair accessible.
Great food and service. Nothing fancy, nothing pretentious, just good food. It is recommended to be there before they open to get in with no wait. Grouper with seafood sauce was spectacular
Food was a lil cold
Great food, great staff, prices very reasonable. Service was a bit slow but adequate, they were very busy and we were not in a hurry so all good. Very much enjoyed our visit and will come back again.
Best food ever. The ocean sauce is amazing !!

I'm so glad a local friend insisted on this place for dinner. It was so amazing! I only wish I hadn't eaten any snacks before coming so I would have been able to eat more. The ocean sauce is a must! Am opportunity not to be missed!
Great food and great service! Specials are a little pricey but worth it!
Food was the best I've ever had!! Will be back no question.

I was looking forward to eating here because it came highly recommend. My group split various entrees (which wasn't really allowed). I got steak with the ocean sauce. The ocean sauce was okay at best, though it was cold. The steak was a "ny strip" but was not tender at all and I ordered it rare. The ocean sauce was an additional $10 which was not communicated. We also ordered the lamb and it was so unbelievably tender. The sauce was good but very salty. The pasta was nothing to write home about. Bland tomatoe sauce, normal linguine. The eggplant parmesan was mediocre, soggy. The crab and corn cannoli was delicious and the sauce with it was beyond amazing. For the reputation of this it honestly was a let down. The wine is cheap though so that's a plus.

Best Italian food. Anywhere. Period. The food was so great I tipped the chefs walking out, who you can see in this very cozy and small restaurant. It's so good that every time I've been there people share their food with the tables around them because it's too good not to share. If you don't love it, you hate great food and a truly unique NoLa experience.

You can’t go wrong with their specialties - the Rack of Lamb and the Stuffed Rainbow Trout with seafood ocean sauce. Service is perfect. We got lucky and slid right into a table without any wait but heard that most night expect 45min-1hr. This is a must-have in New Orleans!
Stuffed flounder was amazing, the lamb was good. Really loud, not romantic. 1:45 wait.

Italian food that was worth the 1 1/2 hour wait in the bar with live music just downstairs.  The stuffed flounder was heavenly.  The garlic bread is what makes Homer drool, Dough!  The smell from the open kitchen will make a full person hungry again.
This was one the most amazing meals we have had so far Bother the rack of lamb and veal were amazing

Long wait to be greeted by an unfriendly server who ushered us downstairs to wait. When we finaly got a table we were told it's only cash!!!!! Why make people wait instead of telling that upfront. Lame
Ocean sauce is excellent! Wait staff was wonderful. A must when in New Orleans!!!
Amazing food. Had fish and there are so many choices.  Great service
Foid and service was outstanding, best meal I've had since being in holiday in America

Outstanding Creole + Italian cuisine, highly recommend getting items that have a Creole inspiration. It's cash only but there is an ATM on premise. Very limited seating and it fills up quickly so make sure to get their early.
The stuffed flounder with Ocean sauce was amazing.  Service was excellent.  One of my favorite places of all time.

Adolfo's is truly amoung the very best Italian restaurants we have ever had the good fortune to thoroughly enjoy. Moreover, the Chicken Marsala is simply to die for. We were told by our waitress the marvelously eccentric artwork that covers the walls  had been sought out and collected by the owner from literally from all over the world.
Great food and staff

Yeez, might as well save a plate and serve me the pepper mill straight up. I started by ordering some kind of pasta but the waitress said it wasn't their specialty (Why it's on the menu, other than wasting my time, beats me). Ah well, alas i tried their fish with "Oceansauce" (I wonder what Ocean have inspired that name?! Is it next to the Dead Sea?) Looked alright, took a bite - Mind you, i enjoy pepper, pepper is good on almost everything. But in moderation, the most peppery dish i make is Carbonara which use a bit more pepper than average. By Odins beard, this "Oceansauce" was abusing the power and might of the pepper. If this is one of their Specialties i'm glad i didn't get the pasta.. okay, when asking the waitress about the quantity of pepper in it,  she kindly remarked that it was a creole / Cajun, magical  excuse to over-season it. Hmm, maybe a one off on account of all these other excellent reviews. But next time, i'm getting a Hotdog or a  Po' Boy
If you get a chance to eat here, do it! Best restaurant in New Orleans hands down! The chef is a god!
How can you give 5 stars for crowded upstairs joint? Ocean sauce.
Fabulous food. Pasta, fish and meat entrees. Bring cash and know there is limited seating.
Hands down the best Chicken Parmesan. Hubby got the lamb.....both were hot, fresh and delicious. We loved it!
Always great food, quaint little restaurant.

Our waitress was passive aggressive telling us we made a bad decision about our order and we should seriously reconsider. We stuck with our decision and the food was fine, pasta wasn’t quite fresh but overall good.
Food here was ridiculous so good and staff where super nice!! Recommend heavily!
Unbelievably good.
The food was very good, everything was a tad spicy (which most of us like!)  Only 11 tables, so very intimate, and away from the main French Quarter.

This is my #1 recommended place. I am ALWAYS telling people to come here. I have never been disappointed in the food and I have eaten here plenty of times. The food is always consistently delicious. Everyone I have ever brought to eat here has felt the same. The restaurant is so charming and quaint. I just adore this place head to toe. 💗

Of the dozens of dining choices in and around New Orleans that I've made over the years, Adolfo's is the best. I recommend grouper with ocean sauce. You're in for a real treat. There is an ATM available and they are above a bar where you can have a drink and anticipate the fireworks that are about to occur on your palate. A+++

We made a reservation in the restaurant for our birthday and were satisfied.  Food and wine are beyond praise. Our waitress didn’t have enough time to spend with us, probably because of busy night at the restaurant. An atmosphere in Adolfo’s very cozy and nice. I liked everything, thanks.

THE BEST meal I have had in a long time. Our waiter was extremely friendly and gave us some local recommendations. Cannot recommend this place enough. Everything was seasoned incredibly and worth every penny.

Best fish in New Orleans.  Very small place.  Get there early.

So disappointed... we came here on a local’s recommendation and waited patiently for a table. Unfortunately for us, we didn’t understand their “no-sharing rule” when we ordered, and took the waitress’s suggestion to “split the plate” (so we wouldn’t waste food). We ended up paying $20 extra to have one meal split onto two plates; and only found out it cost us that much when the bill arrived. When we asked about it, we were shown a piece of paper that said: “sharing is discouraged” - that doesn’t mean it’s mandatory to order a plate per person or CHARGE $20 to split a plate if you don’t. And the food was pretty okay - however, it was not worth the $50 we paid for it!
Mussels in white wine sauce are delicious!

Sorry, but I found this restaurant over-rated, over-hyped, and over-priced.  Ridiculous 2 hr. wait for a table, too.  Too much great and more reasonably priced food and drink in New Orleans to wait around for this one. IMHO. I'm still hung over from the not-so-cheap cheap wine we had there.
Food was amazing. Staff was super friendly. Loved it!

Ordered the special of the day, flounder in ocean sauce. It was extremely spicy and I couldn't eat it. So, I ordered the chicken piccata, which was flavored with butter and salt. I think they forgot to add white wine and garlic. It was tender but extremely disappointing. It came with a salad that had way too much vinegar dressing on it.

This place came highly recommended by a few people we ran into on different tours.  I wish I wouldn’t have wasted my time or money. I’m not sure where all the good reviews come from. If we would have been able to preview a menu online, we probably would have decided not to go.  This part of town was the sketchiest part of New Orleans we visited it. As the concierge at our hotel stated, “only enter Frenchman St through Decatur as the other areas around there are “residential.” I think that was a nice way of saying, DO NOT go anywhere besides Decatur and Frenchman.  We saw the menu after being seated. We had already ordered an appetizer immediately which the waitress recommended. After reviewing the menu further, we decided we really didn’t want to eat here so we wanted to pay for the app and leave. We weren’t “allowed” to. We had to order an entree per person, which made no sense and nowhere did it say that on the menu. So, we were FORCED to pick something off the menu. We didn’t like anything we ordered for our entrees. The pasta my friend got was simply spicy and had no flavor to it. My chicken piccata was fine but nothing special. I can get Italian food at home.  Now, the only reason I give this 2 stars is that a couple sitting close to us had ordered the mussels in garlic sauce (I think it was a special for that day). They had SO MANY mussels. So many they even offered us some. So we tried it, not having mussels before, and it was DELICIOUS. I wish I would have gotten that, but due to their “rules,” so much would have been wasted since we wouldn’t be able to split it.  Also, they are a cash only business.... and they sure do try and talk you into buying the most expensive items on the menu.  I paid 25$ for a piece of chicken, since it is only the chicken. You can choose between a salad or side pasta, but it doesn’t come with any sides itself...
Food is 5, however the line/waiting was about 1 hour, and it is cash only

Get there early at 5:20 for the first seating and you won't wait.  The place fills up in about 10 minites.  Staff was friendly and provided recommendations.  Chicken Picatta was tender and very flavorful.  The Stuffed Flounder and Ocean Sauce special was excellent as well.  Only negative was the crab topping on itit h some small shells and bones?  Not sure how that is, but a good experience overall.  It is loud and crowded, so be warned but that is half the fun of New Orleans.
Intimate Italian restaurant with a cozy atmosphere right on Frenchmen Street. We eat there whenever we have a special occasion. The food and service is consistently excellent!
Stuffed flounder with ocean sauce. Great food but I don't like the face that they make you order one entree per person.  For 3 women it's just way too much food waste.
Fabulous, I am stuffed, it was delicious.  Do the Ocean sauce.

Be prepared with cash for some of the best Italian food around! Upstairs and homey, no reservations are accepted.  So get there before 530 to get on the list for their first seating. We shared the mussels which were to die for! I had grouper Missy and my friend had the chicken parmesan. Both were amazing!! We ended dinner with chocolate mousse cake. Worth every penny and any wait!

After hearing much about this restaurant we headed over early and spent an enjoyable hour downstairs at The Apple Barrel waiting our turn. Once seated in the comfortable dining area we had very delicious and filling appetizers . I had Cannelloni filled with crab and corn which was superb. Nancy had excellent eggplant parmigiana. We should have split one appetizer. The main  courses come with side salad or pasta. I chose the fish of of of.the day, grouper, with the Creole seafood sauce with crawfish and shrimp which was delicious and very creany and filling. My wife had the rack of lamb with ten lamb chops which she was very fond of. The pricing was very reasonable and there is a cash only policy. An ATM is on site for your convenience. Our server was charming and attentive. My dad would always say" you can't go wrong with The New York Strip" . I will have that on my next visit.

We had the lamb, flounder, and veal; all exceptional. Don't believe folks who dis the pasta side that comes before the main--it's meant to be that way, a light and delicate marinara, not a heavy bolognese. Only downside was "45 minute wait" was 1.5 hours.
Second time in 6 mos from out of town (SoCal). THE BEST!!!! Stuffed flounder with Ocean sauce! Absolutely the best meal I’ve ever eaten- PERIOD!

Service was horrible. Their "line management" process is a joke. But if you can get past the fact that you're going to have to wait a minimum of 45 minutes to be seated, then you'll be in for some of the best Italian seafood dishes in New Orleans.
Excellent food
Cozy artistic atmosphere. Escargot, lamb and veal were amazing. There was a 45 min wait but it was well worth it. Downstairs there was a great band and bar which felt like a bonus.
Terrible service. Came in 15 minutes to close to be told no they are not serving food anymore. They don’t close for another 15 min.
This hands down had the best muscles, fish and lamb I’ve ever tried. I almost don’t want to tell anyone about it because the wait was already bad enough.
They suck and are overly priced

Strange experience. The customer service is not their first priority. As a group of 5 we tried to order the 4 entrees, 1 appetizer, and a bottle of wine and were refused service and were told the kitchen wouldn’t serve us. We love to support local businesses but felt uncomfortable and had to leave before they popped the cork.
Great food.  Reasonable prices.  Restaurant fills up quickly.  We got there 15 minutes before opening and waited in line.

Worst most expensive meal ever had. this place was recommended to us and we had high hope. We had the famous lamb chop and it was burnt and tasted mediocre. We also had the veal, but the seafood sauce on the veal was conflicting. The veal was completely covered with sauce and spicy seasoning.  And this place is cash only. SCAM
Excellent meal. Really enjoyed stuffed founder. Fantastic staff
The food was delicious and we didn't mind the wait (only about half an hour at 6:30). I tried lamb for the first time and it was fantastic.
Interesting eclectic menu. Cash only. Small in size. Not H/C accessable.

Found this place purely by accident. Easily one of the best meals that I have ever had in NOLA. I had the NY Strip w/ Ocean Sauce...very recommended. Add in the escargot for an appetizer and some good wine... I cannot wait to visit this place again.

The mussels were amazing! Also, get anything with ocean sauce (you will be glad you did). We arrived a little after 7pm and had to wait for a table, luckily there is a great bar with live music down stairs you get to enjoy while you wait. If you don’t want to wait for a table get there before 7 or around 8 pm.
Great food!  Steak and seafood creole sauce was excellent as well as my wife's chicken panne.  Would definitely go back again!
A local told us to try Adolpho's and it was pure magic. The ocean sauce was transcendent. The space is tiny and lively and brilliant.
Worth the wait!
Top

The waitress was horrible. I never had a waitress count the cash in front of me before... then asked if i was sure that’s what i wanted to leave. I did her itemized math and she rounded it up 2$. She would also literally just drop off a plate and not say anything.  Very disappointed with the service this time... the food was good as always but the waitress counting my cash, asking about her tip and then rounding up 2$ was very inappropriate
Excellent!  Worth the wait!!!!
This was best experience and meal ever!!! I would recommend this to everyone. It's a must if you're in New Orleans
The trout special was one of the best meal's I've ever had
great dinner . a very small place only aboit10 tables so get there early as there are no reservations and its cash only
Stuffed flounder with ocean sauce is one of the best meals I've ever had

Great food at a good value.  I love their ocean sauce, which you can get on just about everything.  Had mine on perfectly cooked NY strip.  Table bread may look plain, but has great garlic flavor.  First come...be prepared to wait.  Great parade route stop

Apparently this restaurant is representative of Creole-Italian food. At least for your first visit get any of their signature entrees with ocean sauce. Both the NY Strip and the stuffed flounder with ocean sauce were out of this world. Service was excellent as well. No reservations but you can enjoy a beverage and live music in the bar downstairs.
Great food on Frenchman street... get there before they open and have a beverage, to have no waiting for your meal

hands down the best restaurant in New Orleans James was my server tonight, great job! I've been coming here for over 10 years the food is excellent get the ocean sauce on anything. tonight I had it covered on it steak it was cooked perfectly rare the way I like it.
Lamb was great. Anything with their Ocean Sauce will be good. Great price. Bar downstairs had an excellent musician
The food was awesome. Our group tried the lamb {med rare}, the stuffed flounder, and New York strip. It was all awesome.

I save 5 star ratings for the truly exceptional,  and this was it. Appetizers as large as entrees at other restaurants. Seafood cream sauce options to top many protein options. My husband's veal parmigiana had zero breading and was excellent as was the stuffed flounder,  my north Atlantic salmon and the new York strip steak (although I thought the only flavor in the steak was from the Ocean sauce [capers w crab & shrimp w crawfish 1/2 each] the member of our party loved it). Will definitely visit again.

My wife and I went to Adolfo's based on all the crazy reviews and recommendations, maybe we went to the wrong Adolfo's?! I wanted a simple pasta or chicken dish but we were talked into getting the stuffed flounder and the rack of lamb. The meals we ordered were presented as specials and didn't have prices listed...we should have asked. Both dishes came with a side of salad  or pasta. Can't comment on the salad but the pasta side was very basic. The lamb costs $38 and the flounder was $24. For the price we paid we expected better quality and taste.

Small restaurant, we got there early to make sure we got in. We had a big plate of mussels in marinara sauce for starters. Then came the rack of lamb, very tender and delicious, also stuffed flounder with their Ocean sauce. It was so good, I could just pour Ocean sauce in my mouth and forget the rest of the meal. You might have to wait in line but it is definitely worth it
Excellent food!!! BUT, It is cash only...ATM in corner so be prepared!
Great meal and wait staff went out of there way way to make sure the experience was good. It didnt disappoint, very impressed. Surf and turf was sensational
My wife and family have been to Adolfo's many times and we love it. We live in the New Orleans area and Adolfo's is one of our favorites. It's worth the wait.
I absolutely love this place.  It's cash only, and usually a 15-20 min wait. Located off Frenchman away from Bourbon.  A must to try!

Be sure to bring cash! Tucked away and not able to make reservation but be there by 5p for a spot and you will not be disappointed. I got the rack of lamb and boy was it the best lamb I’ve ever had (seasoned traveler). Make this a go-to spot
(Translated by Google) Num num num  (Original) Num num num
Waited an hour and a half to be seated and I would wait that long again.

The lamb was so good , the waiter offered to buy the entree from us if we didn't like it  so he could eat it himself!  (Nobody's ever taken him up on that offer). Delicious food,  cool vibe, great service!

You should go here. Expect a wait. Order something with Ocean Sauce. It doesn't matter what. Else, the lamb. Drink some wine. Cash only. Tip well. Feel confident that you made a fantastic choice of restaurants. Best meal I had my last visit. Spent much more elsewhere for less---twice! Pro tip: just line up for opening. Worst case you're waiting at the Apple Barrel bar for an hour.
The food is out of this world!!! Order the mussels for appetizer and anything with their ocean sauce. I can't wait to go back to NOLA and eat at a Adolfo's again!

Worth the wait...and believe me, you will wait!  Their music downstairs was truly awesome coming from just two musicians.  The place is tiny, but it packs a punch.  If you'll be in Nawlins for a few days, you won't be sorry putting this on your list.  And then after dinner, take a walk down Frenchmen Street.  If you're lucky, there'll be an outdoor concert on the next intersection - and they be JAMMIN'!
Such a wonderful Italian restaurant.  The food was phenomenal can't the atmosphere was great.  Excellent service.
Really good Italian food. Ocean sause is to die for.
One of the best meals I can remember. Cozy, fun, great atmosphere, fantastic service.  Don't miss this restaurant!
Adolfo's came recommended and did not disappoint. Ocean Sauce was terrific! Get there before they open!
Tasty food, maybe not worth the wait.

One of the greatest restaurants in New Orleans. The wait is worth it. Don't be in a rush, enjoy some drinks and music downstairs at Apple Barrel and then enjoy fresh, authentic, New Orleans/Italian cuisine in a cozy, romantic atmosphere.

We forgot who tipped us off to this place, but it is our favorite stop for dinner when we visit New Orleans. Service includes folks who know the menu, are able to recommend dishes to suit different tastes, and are friendly and attentive. The food is Italian based, but with a Creole twist. While certain places rely on spicy, and others attract with sweet, Adolpho's has a good understanding of how to use savory flavors to enhance a dish and please the palette.
Cockroaches crawling up the walls.  Did not try food.
Really great place! Rack of Lamb was excellent and the mussels! Friendly service and wonderful atmosphere.
Go. Go with friends and share. Ocean sauce.
Get there early, put your name in and experience the best food this city has to offer. Quaint, romantic, personable service and food you won’t forget, go here!
great food, and service crab and corn caneloni is superb. You must get anything with the ocean sauce.
I had to add salt to everything I ate (3 dishes) and the server was high which made service horrible. Couldn’t get the wine we wanted and was not worth the 2 hour wait.
Simply excellent.  The wait can be long because it literally has 10 tables, but the food is worth it!  The ocean sauce is so delicious and very decadent
Absolutely a no-miss restaurant. Fabulous food always. Never disappointed in 8 years!
Great little upstairs restaurant recommended by a local, for which I'm grateful. Arrive early. They fill up fast. Nice atmosphere delicious food. Great service.
The best.
Overrated. Great location and ambiance but sub par food.
Great little place to eat. Small with a wait.
Awesome dinner spot.  Some of the best food I've had in a long while.
6 Stars..... Unbelievably good!!! Worth the wait. Stuffed flounder with Ocean Sauce.... Just do it
Amazing flavors. Superb service.
Wonderful food! Loved the Ocean Sauce
Loved this place. Was a really great nice last night of vacation dinner place. So good! Cash only...FYI.
Food was okay, but definitely feel like i paid more than I should have. Smaller portions are camouflaged by excessive sauces. Service was excellent, however!
Food and service were excellent. Wines by the glass should be better. Overall, a wonderful experience.

I don't say these words often, but Aldolfo's was the best dining experience I have ever had! I ordered the stuffed flounder special and it was by far the best fish meal I have ever eaten! As an avid fisherman and life-long fan of sea food I have had many excellent meals at many restaurants and at home but this overshadows all! We were lucky enough to have our meal prepared by Adolfo himself and he most certainly didn't disappoint. This was our first trip to New Orleans and this restaurant was suggested by a fellow passenger on our flight who also happened to be a local from the city. The restaurant itself is quite small and seating is very limited but it is truly a fantastic find and if you have the opportunity I highly suggest dining at this establishment!

Great little hidden gem. Cash-only and no reservations taken. Get there early to get on the list to get a table. It's definitely worth the wait. It's a very good way to get to know some of the fusion of cultures that New Orleans is known for. Creole-Italian by way of a little Cajun. At the end of the day, it's tasty and it's cozy :)
Adolfo"s was a hidden gem on Frenchman st. Amazing food, cozy atmosphere, and the bread they serve with dinner is delightful!

Small, but charming restaurant with local vibes. Italian dishes with a creole touch. Fast service. Good food. Just be careful if you are not a spicy food fan: you really beed to let them know ahead and ask about which dishes you could have. They are very helpful though.
Best place to eat in New Orleans.  Only takes cash though
Best Italian I've ever had.
Ok food
Food was awful. Wine was disgusting. Service tried to cheat us out of 30$! Don't dare to go there.
Portions are huge, but not as good as I'd hoped.
Ok tasting but overated

You'll come for the history and reputation of this place but will be blown away by the service and quality of food. Chicken Vincent, as recommended by our server, was incredible. I enjoyed the burps for hours.
The ocean sauce is best thing in NOLA
Great little eatery.  I found it by mistake and very glad I did.  Wait staff was friendly and seemed to really care.  I have extreme food allergies and they made sure to address all concerns.
Ocean Sauce is where it's at.
Unbelievably good food. Totally worth the wait.  Came twice in one week.

Wonderful food.  The house wine was excellent.  A very simple, but elegant upstairs restaurant.  It is small and folks were lined up at 5:30 when it opens.  I recommend steak dishes and the ocean sauce.  Superb.

I have been to a lot of great restaurants in my life.  I have a list of my top 5 meals in my life. Aldolfo's has 2 dinners on that list. It's kinda cheap to eat there but they only take cash... then after dinner, bounce to Snug Harbor.  A great night...

I don't get it. Been here 3 times over the years. The food is okay, you'll probably be a fan if you like butter and cream sauces. The ambiance is cozy. The wait can be annoying. This is on Google's foodie list but I think any foodie would be disappointed

We chose Alfonso's based on advice from our local guide and were very disappointed. The food was ok, but it took forever to get, and when it finally came, they didn't serve the meals together (which, for a table of 2 shouldn't be that hard), and the sauce on my steak wasn't cooked (the mushrooms were still raw). The side salad is part of a salad mix and a few baby spinach leaves thrown in. The side pasta is store-bought pasta with what also tasted like store-bought marinara sauce. All around disappointed for what was a seemingly small, intimate restaurant. Was definitely a tourist trap and the only disappointing meal we had in NOLA.

OMG such a positive surprise and fantastic experience overall, the waitress Natalie was amazing and the food was just delicious perfect and the wine the best in town no question!!!! I will be back and recommend this place for everyone definitely!!!

Took a long time to get a table, so plan to get your name on the list then walk around.  Service is a little slow, but the wait is so worth it. Food is GOOD. Pasta yum and the lamb special with mint sauce, OMG. Definitely try out when in new Orleans.
AMAZING AMAZING FOOD !!!  This was "lick your plate clean" good.  We would come back to New Orleans just to eat here again.  Highly recommend it
Ask for a table and take a seat at the Apple Barrel Bar until it is your time to go upstairs and loosen some notches on your belt.
Awesome food.  Tiny joint, so expect long wait times. It's worth the wait. Great service too.
Fantastic food

Absolute favorite restaurant we tried while we were in NOLA! We even tried a James Beard restaurant and while that was really good, Adolfo's is still my favorite. The food is to die for and you definitely have to try the ocean sauce! The service was also great and our waiter was very helpful with recommendations.  Cash only restaurant, but if you need more cash there is an ATM in the restaurant. Be prepared for a wait on busy nights, you'll have to wait in the bar downstairs for your name to be called which is also cash only, but the food is definitely worth it. My friend and I ordered the mussels which was fresh and delicious, and split the pork chops with ocean sauce. Both were amazing, especially the pork chop! It was tender and cooked just right, and it was a nice healthy portion. The ocean sauce I would have for every meal if I could and it was basically butter, shrimp, blue crab and deliciousness. Wish we could've tried the rack of lamb and the steak, but we didn't have any room. We did get the tiramisu for dessert, which was nice and fluffy. The only thing I wasn't a huge fan of was the garlic bread, but everything else was top notch. I'd definitely come back here again if I'm ever back in the city!
The Ocean sauce!!!! Well worth the wait.

This place was delicious what you looking at was a fish with the Oceana sauce too nice for fillets fried with this delicious sauce on top full of shrimp and whatever it was really good. And it kind of reminds me of the dog vomit when I looked at it LOL but it was the best tasting dog  vomit l ever ate  we had veal with the lemon butter sauce very very good we had the cannoli that was very tasty we had the muscles best mussels I've ever had and oysters Pernod really enjoyed the place in a  hot area  a lot of characters on the street it's all cash but it was worth the trip
Wonderful food. Menu is not extensive, butt service and food were excellent I'm this small upstairs restaurant that has great atmosphere.

Hands down, by far, the one place to treat yourself to an impeccable dinner. No words to describe how phenomenally perfect their rack of lamb tasted. Cash only. Be prepared to wait for a table and be extremely patient in order to truly enjoy your most memorable dining experience.  Tip the staff well. They deserve it.
Found by accident after listening  to some afternoon music at the Apple Barrel.  Yummy food the mussels was awesome and the cannoliloni delish.   A little piece of yummyness in the frenchman area .

Found this place last minute and thank God we did!  The mussels are amazing.  The Stuffed Flounder is incredible! You HAVE to get the White ocean sauce whatever you do!!  Waiter was nice and very knowledgable.  CASH ONLY.   Highly recommend!

We had a lovely dinner at Adolfo’s. The setting is really intimate and cosy, upstairs from a music club called The Apple Barrel.  Our waitress was really friendly and seemed genuinely enthusiastic about the food.  They had plenty of nice-sounding specials on but I was just really in the mood for a simple pasta while my partner opted for a chicken dish, which he really loved. The food isn’t particularly “wow!” or creative beyond having a slight Creole influence in some of the dishes, it’s more like home cooked comfort food, and the prices are quite cheap and the portions were decent, so we were happy. We each had a glass of the house red, which was okay, and shared a piece of limoncello cake for dessert, which was pretty good.  They only take cash but do have an ATM.  If you want some cheap and tasty comfort food in a romantic setting, this place is a decent bet.

Nice waitress and good service but the food was disappointing. I had the flounder with ocean sauce. The whole dish was over cooked and had the texture of a pile of mush. The bathroom was disgusting as well.
Ate here twice on last trip. Their stuffed flounder with Ocean Sauce is the best.
Nasty! Got sick eating the crab canaloni
Outstanding! Wonderful service, amazing food. Definitely will be back❤️
Delicious!
Superb !!

Cute little local Italian spot. They do not take reservations so plan on getting there early...and don't worry if you didn't bring enough cash, they have an ATM right inside. The food is delicious and good for sharing.
Great Place!
Amazing
food was really delicious but kind of expensive.
Best restaurant in New Orleans. There’s a wait, but sitting in the bar downstairs is fun, the prices are all super reasonable, and every dish we’ve tried has been out of this world
Unbelievably delicious and tremendous service!
Now I know why it was so highly recommend! Food and service couldn't have been any better. FANTASTIC!

This place is so special! The service was great. I had the mussels and I couldn't finish them the portion was much. When can you ever say that about a mussel dish? It was so yummy! My husband had the lamb and he ate it all. We didn't have to wait at all, but it was 6 on a Monday. It is a cash only place, so be advised. This will be a staple whenever we are in town.
Great Food ! Thank you for great Service Meridith Hicks!

This is THE best itilian and MAYBE the best food period I have ever had in New Orleans, and that's saying more than alot. Tiny cozy space, and get there as close to opening as you can or expect a LONG wait, but so worth it. Incredible veal, lamb, and fish dishes. Delicate and delicious marinara which is light and pasta that is also tender and perfect. Seriously amazing. Reasonably priced ($$) but CASH ONLY, be aware. Impossibke to beat for their Ocean Sauce and Italian Creole fusion food. A MUST for the foodie in NOLA.
Amazing food. A must when visiting NOLA.
Food was extremely good,  service was good but they only take cash.
Food was great, wonderful little treasure in New Orleans!
Had the chicken Vincent, and the fish Missy (snapper)... OMG... tangy, spicy, delish. Well balanced with the side pasta...  I had my taste of New Orleans cuisine...
No frills place.  Great food.  Italian and Creole cooking.  Worth it!
Great food...small..cozy...great service

100 stars!! Absolutely the best food we ever ate! I had the special of the day: stuffed flounder..oh my gosh, it was delicious. It could have served 2 people, easily. My husband had the steak. He said the sauce was amazing and the steak was excellent! They only take cash, like most places in NOLA, it's just a little pricey..but worth every penny! There's a bar downstairs called Apple Barrel. I had a hurricane and it was the best one I had in the whole town and I had about 6 total in 2 days.
Sharing dishes is discouraged at this place.
Awesome food. What a gem
Fantastic fish, cash only!
Absolutely incredible food. Get there early, the line to get in can be very long.
Great food, great price, great service
One of the BEST meals you can get in New Orleans! Service is amazing as well and price point is right on.

I've heard a ton of good things about this restaurant and didn't experience any of them when I was here. I had the sheep's head fish with ocean sauce. I could forgive it being bland, but I could not forgive the multiple fish scales that I pulled out of my mouth. Also, the waiter's high and mighty attitude was very off putting. The rack of lamb my mom ordered was out of this world though! I probably won't go back given the high price, long wait, cash only, disgusting bathroom (probably the worst in NOLA), and mediocre food, but who am I? They're raking in cash hand over fist and could care less.

Amazing food...the mussels are not to be missed and you can't go wrong with anything that has Ocean Sauce on it. Two things to remember...cash only and you can easily wait over an hour and a half if you're not in line when they open at five thirty sharp.
Small but impressive... mussels, ocean sauce, intimate.  Expect to wait, and there’s not a lot of room in the Apple Barrel Bar downstairs, but it’s worth it.

Wow, what a find!  We went here on the recommendation of a friend.  They told us to arrive early because there would be a wait.  They were right.  We arrived 1/2 hour before the doors opened (in the rain no less) and we got one of the last tables.  Awesome food!!  You would never guess just by looking at the place that the food would be so world class.  It's a total divey upstairs room that used to be an apartment.  Very cool, very NOLA!
Very good.
I’ve eaten at many places in this world and Adolfo’s is one near the top of my list. And very reasonable prices.
I've eaten here probably a dozen or more times. I have never had an average meal, it's always outstanding. A great hidden gem!
All said and done, it was kind of pricey. But, hands down great food! Service was good, and cleanliness was comparable to the rest of New Orleans.
Gastric Nirvana.  Great service!

If you're thinking of eating here, please do yourself a favour and come and try it. Yes you have to wait, but there's a bar downstairs with generous pours and music, so you'll be fine. The food is so, so delicious. Get the off menu specials, take the recommendations, you won't regret it. Bre is awesome! Let's hope you are lucky enough to be served by her!
Love this place
The best!
Horrible service

I wish I could have taken a picture of our food, it was amazing! Our server, Brianna (I think? I know it was Bre), was so nice, She didn't make us feel rushed, and she her recommendations of the Mussels and Rack of Lamb, was amazing! I had mine with salad and my boyfriend with pasta. When I asked her a question, she asked the rest of the staff and told me the best shops to go at the time. As for the cook, all I can say is WOW! The whole staff was amazing. This was worth the small wait cause of how busy it was, and it was worth the price 100%, best date ever. My boyfriend and I plan to come back again next year
Delicious, authentic Italian food.  Fantastic service
Best rack of lamb I've ever tasted! Supurb!

Hands down some of the best food in New Orleans. If you don't call ahead for a reservation, you have to put your name on a list to make it inside. We waited for an hour and a half but it was so worth it! We had the steak in ocean sauce and their snapper also in the ocean sauce with an order of escargot as an appetizer. From our meal, the garlic bread, wine, and family feel, we had a great time. Just make sure you bring a wad of cash as it is cash only. You will spend an average of $50 per person so be mindful. They do have an atm available though, so no worries. I will absolutely return to this delicious place.  So worth everything
Excellent Italian-Creole dishes. Cash only, ATM onsite.
Top 10 restaurant I've been to in the world. Food and atmosphere unbeatable anywhere

One of my favorite New Orleans spots. Busy place and no reservations, put your name down and head to the bar downstairs to listen to some music. CASH only in both places, husband owns the restaurant upstairs, wife has the bar downstairs.
The best place in New Orleans for traditional NOLA food.
Great food, great service. We were there a little early so wait was only 20 minutes.
This place has amazing food!!! The ocean sauce is the bomb! Don’t let this place go by stop and eat great food
Disorganized and overcrowded but always worth the wait.
Excellent food and a fair price for the location.
Incredible food and service.
What a meal this was. The white wine muscles were the best I've ever had and both dishes were amazing. Be sure you get an entree that has the ocean sauce.
Maybe I'm bad at ordering... But every item I had was greasy and mundane... Bread particularly awful.
phenomenal eats!!!

Very intimate spot, food looks amazing, nice portions, service was great, that helped a lot. The food, maybe I'm being to critical but it was lacking the flavor I'm used to getting in New Orleans, but that's just my opinion, everyone else enjoyed theirs.
Expensive, mediocre food. Coops is much better

I had supper here the other night with 3 other people.  I would say this place is just okay.  It was about an hour wait because it i's a small quaint restaurant.  The bottom floor had a bar and live music and is fun.  Keep in mind the bar and restaurant is cash only.  They do have 2 ATMs for you to use as well.  I,ordered the lamb, it was cooked perfectly and was tender but lacked flavor.  It seemed like it had some oil and rosemary but no real flavor.  It came with a side of pasta which was noodles and spaghetti sauce and it was horrible.  Sauce was so watery and flavor lacking. We also got the flounder with crab meat and ocean sauce.  Flavor was okay but left more to be desired especially for the price.  We also go the salmon which was liked and a eggplant parmesian which was also awful similar to the other pasta.  Again sauce was very watery and the entire plate lacked flavoring.  We also sat under and AC vent that was covered in mold that kept dripping water on our table.  We told the waitress and she replied with "well there's nothing we can do about that".  A bit disapppinting that she didn't offer to move our seat or any other resolution.  I would not go back.
Great food
Great atmosphere and staff, not good food.  I suppose, you don't go to New Orleans for Italian though. They also only take cash...IRS might want to go eat dinner there maybe?
Amazing food, attentive staff, fair prices. Be ready to wait... this place is always packed.
The rack of lamb was the best ever...The Best!!! Bring cash. No credit cards...Frenchman st. The place to BE.

My go-to whenever I'm in New Orleans. No reservations, a small dining room with (at last count) 9 tables, you line up at 6 and if you're lucky you can eat by 9 ... and it is worth every minute. Anything with Ocean Sauce is what to order -- be very nice to your server, to offset the morons who think they can jump the line (they won't).

The service was just awful! We waited 45 minutes between appetizers and the main course. The server never even came to the table once. The veal was way overdone and the flounder actually disenegrated.  The bread wasn’t toasted, had no garlic and was stale. I would NEVER recommend this restaurant to anyone! A relatively popular "hole in the wall" venue.  The bar downstairs was small with a live guitar and piano.  It was standing room only at 4 pm.  The cuisine upstairs was amazing.  It was the last meal I had in 2017 and it was the best meal I had all year.  You can't make a reservation so it's first come, first serve.  We showed up at 4 and the doors didn't open until 5:30. If you have.bad experience at Adolfo you are either very unlucky or a spoiled brat. The building is as old as the city but that has nothing to do with the top shelf quality of food and service. This place is a hidden trasuure of the Quarter. The rustic old fashioned setting reminds me of a scene from the Godfather movie where Michael Coreloni whacks the police captain. Just go there, you will love it.

We got the Adolfo’s at 5:25 pm and there were 10 people ahead of us on a Saturday afternoon. They have 11 tables or about 34 covers. The place was completely full at opening. Calin our waiter was outstanding. Food came out to the first tables a little fast, but but the time we were served our entree’s came out at just the fight time to enjoy out appetizer and salad. We had the mussels for our appetizer and the were excellent in a garlic butter sauce similar to a barbecue shrimp sauce. We then had the stuffed flounder and pork chops for entrees. The portion for the pork chop was about 2 pounds of very succulent and delicious lightly smoked pork covered with their signature ocean sauce. The stuffed flounder was also a large portion and also covered with ocean sauce. I was very impressed with the consistence and flavor of the stuffed flounder because of how evenly the fish and stuffing was cooked throughout. These people have a very high quality food and service and we will definitely be back and recommend to anyone looking for superb food in a casual atmosphere.
